1 A BILL for an Act to create and enact chapter 6-08.6 of the North Dakota Century Code, relating
2 to the Uniform Special Deposits Act; and to provide for application.
3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
4 SECTION 1. Chapter 6-08.6 of the North Dakota Century Code is created and enacted as
5 follows:
6 6 - 08.6 - 01. Definitions .
7 In this chapter:
8 1. "Account agreement" means an agreement that:
9 a. Is in a record between a bank or credit union and one or more depositors;
10 b. May have one or more beneficiaries as additional parties; and
11 c. States the intention of the parties to establish a special deposit in accordance
12 with this chapter.
13 2. "Bank" means a trust company or a person engaged in the business of banking as
14 defined in section 6 - 01 - 02 .
15 3. "Beneficiary" means a person that:
16 a. Is identified as a beneficiary in an account agreement; or
17 b. If not identified as a beneficiary in an account agreement, may be entitled to
18 payment from a special deposit:
19 (1) Under the account agreement; or
20 (2) On termination of the special deposit.
21 4. "Contingency" means an event or circumstance stated in an account agreement which
22 is not certain to occur but must occur before the bank or credit union is obligated to
23 pay a beneficiary.
