1 6 - 08.6 - 02. Scope - Choice of law - Forum .
2 1. This chapter applies to a special deposit under an account agreement that states the
3 intention of the parties to establish a special deposit governed by this chapter,
4 regardless of whether a party to the account agreement or a transaction related to the
5 special deposit, or the special deposit itself, has a reasonable relation to this state.
6 2. The parties to an account agreement may choose a forum in this state for settling a
7 dispute arising out of the special deposit, regardless of whether a party to the account
8 agreement or a transaction related to the special deposit, or the special deposit itself,
9 has a reasonable relation to this state.
10 3. This chapter does not affect:
11 a. A right or obligation relating to a deposit other than a special deposit under this
12 chapter; or
13 b. The voidability of a deposit or transfer that is fraudulent or voidable under other
14 law.
15 6 - 08.6 - 03. Variation by agreement or amendment .
16 1. The effect of sections 6 - 08.6 - 01 through 6 - 08.6 - 05, 6 - 08.6 - 07 through 6 - 08.6 - 10, and
17 6 - 08.6 - 13 may not be varied by agreement, except as provided in those sections .
18 Subject to subsection 2, the effect of sections 6 - 08.6 - 06, 6 - 08.6 - 11, and 6 - 08.6 - 12 may
19 be varied by agreement.
20 2. A provision in an account agreement or other record that substantially excuses liability
21 or substantially limits remedies for failure to perform an obligation under this chapter is
22 not sufficient to vary the effect of a provision of this chapter.
23 3. If a beneficiary is a party to an account agreement, the bank or credit union and the
24 depositor may amend the agreement without the consent of the beneficiary only if the
25 agreement expressly permits the amendment.
26 4. If a beneficiary is not a party to an account agreement and the bank or credit union
27 and the depositor know the beneficiary has knowledge of the agreement's terms, the
28 bank or credit union and the depositor may amend the agreement without the consent
29 of the beneficiary only if the amendment does not adversely and materially affect a
30 payment right of the beneficiary.
