6 6 - 08.6 - 04. Requirements for special deposit .
7 A deposit is a special deposit if it is:
8 1. A deposit of funds in a bank or credit union under an account agreement;
9 2. For the benefit of at least two beneficiaries, one or more of which may be a depositor;
10 3. Denominated in a medium of exchange that is currently authorized or adopted by a
11 domestic or foreign government;
12 4. For a permissible purpose stated in the account agreement; and
13 5. Subject to a contingency.
14 6 - 08.6 - 05. Permissible purpose .
15 1. A special deposit must serve at least one permissible purpose stated in the account
16 agreement from the time the special deposit is created in the account agreement until
17 termination of the special deposit.
18 2. If, before termination of the special deposit, the bank or credit union or a court
19 determines the special deposit no longer satisfies subsection 1, sections 6 - 08.6 - 07
20 through 6 - 08.6 - 10 cease to apply to any funds deposited in the special deposit after
21 the special deposit ceases to satisfy subsection 1 .
22 3. If, before termination of a special deposit, the bank or credit union determines the
23 special deposit no longer satisfies subsection 1, the bank or credit union may take
24 action the bank or credit union believes is necessary under the circumstances,
25 including terminating the special deposit.
26 6 - 08.6 - 06. Payment to beneficiary by bank or credit union .
27 1. Unless the account agreement provides otherwise, the bank or credit union is
28 obligated to pay a beneficiary if there are sufficient actually and finally collected funds
29 in the balance of the special deposit.
30 2. Except as provided in subsection 3, the obligation to pay the beneficiary is excused i f
31 the funds available in the special deposit are insufficient to cover the payment.
