1 3. Unless the account agreement provides otherwise, if the funds available in the special
2 deposit are insufficient to cover an obligation to pay a beneficiary, a beneficiary may
3 elect to be paid the funds that are available or, if there is more than one beneficiary, a
4 pro rata share of the funds available. Payment to the beneficiary making the election
5 under this subsection discharges the bank's or credit union's obligation to pay a
6 beneficiary and does not constitute an accord and satisfaction with respect to another
7 person obligated to the beneficiary.
8 4. Unless the account agreement provides otherwise, the obligation of the bank or credit
9 union obligated to pay a beneficiary is immediately due and payable.
10 5. The bank or credit union may discharge the bank's or credit union's obligation under
11 this section by:
12 a. Crediting another transaction account of the beneficiary; or
13 b. Taking other action that:
14 (1) Is allowed under the account agreement for the bank or credit union to
15 obtain a discharge; or
16 (2) Otherwise would constitute a discharge under law.
17 6. If the bank or credit union obligated to pay a beneficiary has incurred an obligation to
18 discharge the obligation of another person, the obligation of the other person is
19 discharged if action by the bank or credit union under subsection 5 would constitute a
20 discharge of the obligation of the other person under law that determines whether an
21 obligation is satisfied.
22 6 - 08.6 - 07. Property interest of depositor or beneficiary .
23 1. A depositor or a beneficiary does not have a property interest in the special deposit
24 itself.
25 2. The only property interest with respect to a special deposit is the right to receive
26 payment if the bank or credit union is obligated to pay a beneficiary. Any property
27 interest under this subsection is determined under other law.
28 6 - 08.6 - 08. When creditor process is enforceable against bank or credit union .
29 1. Subject to subsection 2, creditor process with respect to a special deposit is no t
30 enforceable against the bank or credit union holding the special deposit.
