1 2. Creditor process is enforceable against the bank or credit union holding a special
2 deposit with respect to an amount the bank or credit union is obligated to pay a
3 beneficiary or a depositor if the process:
4 a. Is served on the bank or credit union;
5 b. Provides sufficient information to allow the bank or credit union to identify the
6 depositor or the beneficiary from the bank's or credit union's books and records;
7 and
8 c. Gives the bank or credit union a reasonable opportunity to act on the process.
9 3. Creditor process served on a bank or credit union before it is enforceable against the
10 bank or credit union under subsection 2 does not create a right of the creditor agains t
11 the bank or credit union or a duty of the bank or credit union to the creditor. Other law
12 determines whether creditor process creates a lien enforceable against the beneficiary
13 on a contingent interest of a beneficiary, including a depositor as a beneficiary, even if
14 not enforceable against the bank or credit union.
15 6 - 08.6 - 09. Injunction or similar relief .
16 A court may enjoin, or grant similar relief that would have the effect of enjoining, a bank or
17 credit union from paying a depositor or beneficiary only if payment would constitute a material
18 fraud or facilitate a material fraud with respect to a special deposit.
19 6 - 08.6 - 10. Recoupment or set off .
20 1. Except as provided in subsection 2 or 3, a bank or credit union may not exercise a
21 right of recoupment or set off against a special deposit.
22 2. An account agreement may allow the bank or credit union to debit the special deposit:
23 a. When the bank or credit union becomes obligated to pay a beneficiary, in an
24 amount that does not exceed the amount necessary to discharge the obligation;
25 b. For a fee assessed by the bank or credit union that relates to an overdraft in the
26 special deposit account;
27 c. For costs incurred by the bank or credit union that relate directly to the special
28 deposit; or
29 d. To reverse an earlier credit posted by the bank or credit union to the balance of
30 the special deposit account, if the reversal occurs under an event or
31 circumstance warranted under other law governing mistake and restitution.
