1 3. The bank or credit union holding a special deposit may exercise a right of recoupment
2 or set off against an obligation to pay a beneficiary, even if the bank or credit union
3 funds payment from the special deposit.
4 6 - 08.6 - 11. Duties and liability of bank or credit union .
5 1. A bank or credit union does not have a fiduciary duty to any person with respect to a
6 special deposit.
7 2. When the bank or credit union holding a special deposit becomes obligated to pay a
8 beneficiary, a debtor-creditor relationship arises between the bank or credit union and
9 beneficiary.
10 3. The bank or credit union holding a special deposit has a duty to a beneficiary to
11 comply with the account agreement and this chapter.
12 4. If the bank or credit union holding a special deposit does not comply with the account
13 agreement or this chapter, the bank or credit union is liable to a depositor or
14 beneficiary only for damages proximately caused by the noncompliance. Except as
15 provided by other law, the bank or credit union is not liable for consequential, special,
16 or exemplary damages.
17 5. The bank or credit union holding a special deposit may rely on records presented in
18 compliance with the account agreement to determine whether the bank or credit union
19 is obligated to pay a beneficiary.
20 6. If the account agreement requires payment on presentation of a record, the bank or
21 credit union shall determine within a reasonable time whether the record is sufficient to
22 require payment. If the agreement requires action by the bank or credit union on
23 presentation of a record, the bank or credit union is not liable for relying in good faith
24 on the genuineness of the record if the record appears on its face to be genuine.
25 7. Unless the account agreement provides otherwise, the bank or credit union is not
26 required to determine whether a permissible purpose stated in the agreement
27 continues to exist.
28 6 - 08.6 - 12. Term and termination .
29 1. Unless otherwise provided in the account agreement, a special deposit terminates five
30 years after the date the special deposit was first funded.
