1 2. Unless otherwise provided in the account agreement, if the bank or credit union
2 cannot identify or locate a beneficiary entitled to payment when the special deposit is
3 terminated, and a balance remains in the special deposit, the bank or credit union
4 shall pay the balance to the depositor as a beneficiary.
5 3. A bank or credit union that pays the remaining balance as provided under subsection 2
6 has no further obligation with respect to the special deposit.
7 6 - 08.6 - 13. Principles of law and equity .
8 Title 41, consumer protection law, law governing deposits generally, law related to eschea t
9 and abandoned or unclaimed property, and the principles of law and equity, including law
10 related to capacity to contract, principal and agent, estoppel, fraud, misrepresentation, duress,
11 coercion, mistake, and bankruptcy, supplement this chapter except to the extent inconsistent
12 with this chapter.
13 6 - 08.6 - 14. Uniformity of application and construction .
14 In applying and construing this chapter, a court shall consider the promotion of uniformity of
15 the law among the states that enact it.
16 SECTION 2. APPLICATION. This Act applies to:
17 1. A special deposit made under an account agreement executed after July 31, 2025;
18 and
19 2. A deposit made under an agreement executed before August 1, 2025, if:
20 a. All parties entitled to amend the agreement agree to make the deposit a special
21 deposit governed by chapter 6-08.6; and
22 b. The special deposit referenced in the amended agreement satisfies section
23 6-08.6-04.
